    "This approach increased domain adaptation efficiency by 37%, while still preserving the model's generalization capabilities.",
    "The system's ability to generalize stylistically was tested across different domains.",
    "As shown in Table 7, the Grammar Correction module maintained stable performance across academic papers, business emails, and creative writing (F1 score variation < 4.2%).",
    "However, the Lexical Optimization module had more limited applicability in creative writing, with a 19.8% drop in suggestion acceptance rate, largely due to metaphorical expressions that were outside the training data distribution.",
    "Notably, the Content Coherence module showed the greatest improvement in academic writing (+ 32.6%) compared to business emails (+ 12.3%), reflecting the differing demands for logical rigor across genres."
